{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "booking-platform-docker",
		"name": "Booking Platform - Docker Services",
		"description": "Health checks and verification requests for the Dockerized booking platform.\n\n## How to use\n\n1. Start the platform: `docker compose -f infrastructure/docker/docker-compose.yaml up --build`\n2. Wait for all containers to reach healthy status\n3. Run the requests in order — start with Health Checks to verify all services are up\n4. Then run the GraphQL API requests (same as local, but through Docker containers)\n\n## Port mappings\n\n| Service | Port |\n|---|---|\n| config-service | 8888 |\n| eureka-service | 8761 |\n| graphql-gateway | 8080 |\n| user-service | 8081 |\n| event-service | 8082 |\n| booking-service | 8083 |\n| payment-service | 8084 |\n| notification-service | 8086 |\n| analytics-service | 8087 |\n| ticket-service | 8088 |\n\n## Differences from local collection\n\n- Keycloak runs on port 8180 (same as local)\n- All services communicate internally via Docker network\n- gRPC mTLS is disabled (plaintext within Docker network)\n- Config server URL is overridden via CONFIG_SERVER_URL env var",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
	"variable": [
		{
			"key": "baseUrl",
			"value": "http://localhost:8080",
			"type": "string"
		},
		{
			"key": "accessToken",
			"value": "",
			"type": "string"
		},
		{
			"key": "refreshToken",
			"value": "",
			"type": "string"
